{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1156352, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Egrem", "body": "Al'Akir is the Lord of Air and the weakest of the four major Elemental Lords (the others being Ragnaros the Firelord, Therazane the Stonemother, and Neptulon the Tidehunter).\r\n\r\nThe Elemental Lords led the armies of the Old Gods until they were defeated by the titans and banished to the Elemental Plane.  Now Al'Akir rules Skywall from the Throne of the Four Winds, where he is encountered in [i]Cataclysm[/i].", "date": "2010-10-29T19:29:41-05:00", "rating": 116, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I suppose no-one has so far noticed that at the end of the Ozumat encounter the \"powerful\" Neptulon is kidnapped once again by the giant squid and brought away from the Throne of Tides. Didn't you feel strange that once beaten the beast and awarded the loot you receive no greetings, no aknowledgement from the Lord of Water? This is because he is not with you anymore! And maybe this can open scenarios of future patches with raids in Vash'jir or related to the Water Plane just like the Firelands. Who knows? Sure is that while Al'Akir carries on wiping raids, Ragnaros waits in Sulfuron Keep and T", "creationdate": "2010-10-29T19:29:42-05:00", "id": 484482, "rating": 25, "commentid": 1156352, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ixifer", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I don't care what the lore says, this guy is definitely not the weakest elemental lord.  Why?  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=40792#comments]Al'akir doesn't need my help to avoid being beaten to death by murlocs...[/url]", "creationdate": "2011-01-06T12:38:03-06:00", "id": 212413, "rating": 154, "commentid": 1156352, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "275441", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Except that prior to that fight Neptulon was weakened by corrupt water from all the Naga and the Leviathan.   The moment you uncorrupt his water, you get that massive buff, and even should you be bad enough to not outright kill the leviathan then, if one member manages to survive long enough, Neptulon will 1 shot it.", "creationdate": "2011-01-09T20:06:49-06:00", "id": 213701, "rating": 68, "commentid": 1156352, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Brakkis", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"I don't care what the lore says, this guy is definitely not the weakest elemental lord.  Why?  Al'akir doesn't need my help to avoid being beaten to death by murlocs...\"  Murlocs MUST be nerfed!  EDIT: Everyone's up rating me! No one likes murlocs! D: :(", "creationdate": "2011-02-18T21:16:56-06:00", "id": 226309, "rating": 76, "commentid": 1156352, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nintendorichard", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Exactly correct, Ixifer. However, since Naga are just another vampiric power craving nabs, they will just use Neptulon's power. Possible outcomes: 1. Another rescue(doubt it) 2. Fight against subdued Neptulon(good chance) 3. Fight against same Octopus with Neptulon's gift(aka Sinestra) 4. Fight against some Monstrousity(Neptulon completely drained to power it).", "creationdate": "2011-06-08T07:11:12-05:00", "id": 244819, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1156352, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wirxaw", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 1157229, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "339177", "body": "I love the model for Al'Akir, and the sword he's wielding looks fantastic. Not much in the way of abilities or strategies right now, but  [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Te5UxxpxKyw]here's a video of Paragon defeating Al'Akir 25-man during the beta.[/url] This guy is freaking HUGE!\r\n\r\nYou also get the \"of the Four Winds\" title when defeating Al'Akir on heroic difficulty.\r\n\r\n\r\nLooks like a fun fight, and I cant wait to try him out.  :)", "date": "2010-10-30T23:46:36-05:00", "rating": 27, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
