{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 1251032, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nethris", "body": "How to: Al'Akir (Normal)\n\nThis is a perfect example why some bosses are SO MUCH easier on 10man than in 25man (thanks a lot blizzard for having exactly the same damage in both, but with 25man being 5x harder). In 10man, spread equally on all sides, 2 healers is doable, 3 is fine as well. I suggest either 1 tank/3 heal/6 dps or 2 tank/2heal/6 dps, 2tank/3heal/5dps really isnt needed. In 25, 2 tanks, 6-7 healers and rest dps.\n\nPhase 1 (100-80%)\n\nThe key here is to spread like CRAAAAAZY. In 10man, make single stacks and spread healers equally to be able to heal everyone. In 25, make stacks of 2's and 3's, the damage is pretty crazy compared to 10man but you just gotta heal it. Boss doesnt hit tank very hard at all.\n\nAs for abilities, he spawns a random lightning web thingie that chains to everyone inside it, hitting for 20k for every player inside. So make sure you move ONLY front/back and not sideways when moving (sometimes you have to, but just avoid it generally).\nWhen Wind Burst casts, move closer to boss, deals ~40k dmg to everyone and knocks them back.\nDont stand under blizzard (the blizzard itself doesnt hurt, but the ice on ground doe and slows).\nWhen tornados circle around the platform, find the gap between them and go through it to avoid getting grabbed by them. This is all about invidual skill, everyone must be aware of tornados coming from both sides.\n\nPhase 2 (80-25 (30?)%)\n\nChain lightning web of doom stops, so everyone move to one side of the boss, with tank on one end, melee dps on other and ranged in between.\nTornados from P1 still spawn, they also spawn faster so you might have 2 up at the same time. Wind burst is gone (Not 100% sure on this, cant remember atm), but little adds called stormlings spawn. Offtank or a dps with a taunt (DK in BloodP is <3) grab them and keep them away from the raid and bring them down one by one after 3 of them are spawned. On death, they will debuff boss with 10% damage taken, which stacks, so make sure you dont instantly kill the first one that spawns but wait a little bit.\nThere will also be a debuff called Acid Rain which stacks as long as phase 2 lasts, dealing increasing damage to everyone in the raid (the stacks can be reseted with AMS/bubble/block). Pop hero/bl somewhere around halfway through p2, its not really needed in p3.\n\nPhase 3 (till 0)\n\nEveryone flies in to the air, boss is untankable. This is really a lot easier than any of the phases, it just looks like it could be hard. Start by having EVERYONE move UP, towards the altitude of the bosses head. Set up some raid marks to keep everyone at the same level. When storm clouds spawn, move downwards a bit. When lightning appears around someone, move away from him. Rinse and repeat until boss is dead. If you get too close to the bottom, simply move through the lightning cloud, the damage isnt even that bad.\n\nMechanically the best fight in the first tier (par sinestra possibly), but phase 3 is a bit of a let down.", "date": "2010-12-21T20:25:58-06:00", "rating": 132, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "We killed it about week ago in 10m, the most important think in first phase are spacing between ppls. Groups of 2 looks like best option. In second phase assign one dps to stormling and kill them right before feedback is about expire.  We wiped there couple times, but it isnt realy hard encounter.  [b]Kill video[/b]: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iQo7x7m39hQ", "creationdate": "2010-12-31T02:48:33-06:00", "id": 471697, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1251032, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LoRDN3o", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If your front groups are having trouble dodging the wind burst + tornado combination, try having your tank to eat an electrocute with full CD during the first tornado(if the gap is outside his hitbox) or partial electrocute through the second tornado.  This'll make sure the wind burst isn't casted until the tornado is past your tank.", "creationdate": "2011-03-09T23:13:20-06:00", "id": 231202, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1251032, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "cywang86", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just a theory, but does anyone know if using [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=56850]Deepstone Oil[/url] when knocked back by Wind Burst (or possibly even the tornadoes) can freeze you in midair, causing you to land safely on the platform after dispelling it?  Was gonna try it tonight in TotFW, but we disbanded before I could give it a genuine attempt.", "creationdate": "2011-08-13T23:04:31-05:00", "id": 258459, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1251032, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sfangcleaveftw", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Quoting the OP: \"As for abilities, he spawns a random lightning web thingie that chains to everyone inside it, hitting for 20k for every player inside. So make sure you move ONLY front/back and not sideways when moving (sometimes you have to, but just avoid it generally).\" Link: http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93256 (Lightning Strike). It's a 60 degree conical attack. That's why you spread out, that and to hopefully play follow the leader on the spaces between the Squall Line (http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87856).", "creationdate": "2012-06-14T18:38:26-05:00", "id": 549867, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1251032, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Hairband", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupD