{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 1255202, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Myhv", "body": "If you are a healer you'll be frustrated in this fight like no other...  So many things to watch out, not to mention ridiculously annoying interrupt debuff that you'll get every time you run close to the boss. And spiky damage in first phase. \r\n\r\nBut the most annoying part will be that sometimes you just can't do anything and you can't controll what is happening. Like when you have to run close to the boss to avoid knock back, you have to run through ice patches. You barely make it in time but tornadoes spawn close to you and you are knocked back in to them. After you got thrown away by tornado, you come back on the platform just to get knocked back out again by next wind burst.\r\n\r\nAfter spending 2 hours there today I really don't want to go back.", "date": "2010-12-23T17:12:56-06:00", "rating": 35, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Pretty much, 'avoidable' damage that is not avoidable is a bull!@#$ mechanic to make bosses seem harder.", "creationdate": "2011-01-26T20:04:58-06:00", "id": 476259, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1255202, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "201535", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
