{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 1284550, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "456163", "body": "[quote]By Lasengnomad 18 days ago (Patch 4.0.3)\r\n...It's nice to hear that many players are still chomping at the bit for a challenge...[/quote]\r\n\r\nIt's, \"Champing at the bit.\"  Sorry, but that's a pet peeve of mine.", "date": "2011-01-08T17:45:34-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Being as \"chomp\" is a different (and more well known) form of \"champ\" I fail to see why it matters. Please don't stomp off because you are irritated that is just my opinion. (although I guess you would \"stamp off\" instead of stomping but I digress)", "creationdate": "2012-01-23T12:24:55-06:00", "id": 511446, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1284550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "285271", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 1307873, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "GraveDiggerX", "body": "[url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-s1q70iUicA]Strategy Guide & Video:[/url]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Below I have written a guide as well as demonstrate how we did this boss.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n[b][u]Our Group:[/u][/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]1 Tank - | Druid |[/li]\r\n[li]3 Healers - | Paladin | Druid | Priest |[/li]\r\n[li]6 DPS - | Ele Shaman | SPriest | Hunter x2 | Death Knight | Rogue[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n[b][u]General Boss Information:[/u][/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]This boss is a 3 phase encounter.[/li]\r\n[li]He uses the power of wind to try and destroy the raid.[/li]\r\n[li]It is a fairly simple encounter and very lenient on damage requirement.[/li]\r\n[li]If no one is in melee range, he will cast [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=88427]Electrocute[/url] until someone returns/gets in melee range.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n[b][u]Boss Abilities:[/u][/b]\r\n\r\n[b]---Phase 1: (100%-80%)[/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]You first begin the encounter by damaging Al. Be careful not to pull. You cannot face pull.[/li]\r\n[li]Before the pull you will want to split your raid up into 5 groups (2 people on each of the Fleur de Lis looking areas on the platform) due to his ability [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93257]Lightning Strike[/url].  This ability looks like a blanket on the platform and comes outward from Al'Akir in a cone. It will chain to everyone in the area. Make sure each player in the raid can be reached by at least one healer.[/li]\r\n[li]In addition, Al will spawn two [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87856]Squall Lines[/url] which are columns of tornadoes rotating around the platform. One will be rotating clockwise, and the other will be counterclockwise. They are alternated on their spawn times and they will make one orbit around the platform before disappearing. The way to avoid this is by the one absent tornado in the line, ideally, by running through the opening. If you touch a tornado, you will be caught in the vortex for a few seconds, taking ~40k damage per second. The only way out of this is the Priest's ability [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=73325]Leap of Faith[/url].[/li]\r\n[li]Furthermore, Al'Akir will cast [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93260]Ice Storm[/url]... A blizzard mechanic that leaves an ice patch on the ground. Easily avoidable, so do so.[/li]\r\n[li]Finally, the last ability in P1 is [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87770]Wind Burst[/url]. This ability has a cast time, and to avoid being knocked off the platform, you must move in before the cast is complete. It knocks players back about 3/4 the platform. Be careful with tornado and wind burst timing... don't get wind burst into a tornado. Run through ice if you need to.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]---Phase 2: (80%-25%)[/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]During the transition into this phase, have everyone converge to the middle and stack in a triangle. Ranged out, Tank and Melee in melee range about 20 yards apart.[/li]\r\n[li]The reason you want to stack in this phase is to alleviate pain on the healer's part due to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93281]Acid Rain[/url], which persists throughout the phase and places a stacking debuff on every raid member.[/li]\r\n[li]In addition, Al'Akir will spawn a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=47175]Stormling[/url] every 25 seconds or so. They need to be killed, and once killed they will apply [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87904]Feedback[/url] to Al'Akir which increases his damage taken by 10% and stacks indefinitely.[/li]\r\n[li]Squall Lines continue to spawn in P2.[/li]\r\n[li]Wind Burst is [b]NOT[/b] cast in P2.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n[b]---Phase 3: (25%-0%)[/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]During the transition into this phase, Al will shatter the platform and everyone will gain an [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=89107]Eye of the Storm[/url] buff which increases movement speed by 300% and allows everyone to fly.[/li]\r\n[li]At this time, you will want to have someone marked to stack on horizontally, like you would in the Malygos encounter. This is due to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93298]Lightning Clouds[/url], which is spawned at the altitude of a random player. After the cloud is cast, you have a few seconds to elevate before it erupts in lightning.[/li]\r\n[li]However, while stacked you need to be aware of the player with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=89668]Lightning Rod[/url]. This is similar to a Shaman's Thunderstorm and will damage players within 20yards.[/li]\r\n[li]Additionally, he will begin to cast Wind Burst again. Move in to prevent being knocked back into the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=89104]Relentless Storm[/url]. This will trap you for 6 seconds and cause nature damage.[/li]\r\n[li]Burn him down and you will have your kill![/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n[b][u]Tips:[/u][/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Avoid tornadoes.[/li]\r\n[li]Time Stormling deaths for Feedback stacks.[/li]\r\n[li]Don't be bad.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nI wish you the best of luck, and feel free to critique my post and ask any questions.\r\n\r\nPlease uprate if this helped at all!\r\n\r\nA link to our video on YouTube is [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-s1q70iUicA]HERE[/url] so you can see how it's done. Please rate and subscribe to see our upcoming videos!\r\n\r\n~[url=http://us.battle.net/wow/en/character/executus/wr%C3%A8x/advanced]Wrex[/url] | [url=http://www.guildox.com/go/g.asp?n=Pseudonym&r=Executus-US]Pseudonym[/url] | Executus-US", "date": "2011-01-24T11:28:37-06:00", "rating": 66, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 1312550, "nreplies": 12, "sticky": 0, "user": "NobodyYouKnow", "body": "A little warning to warriors: don't heroic leap while standing on the platform that Al'Akir is. \n\n[small]Al'akir's hit box is ridiculously large. Your heroic leap will hit the boss and start the fight.[/small]", "date": "2011-01-27T22:25:57-06:00", "rating": 36, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[b]Mages: [/b]Mages can blink through the tornadoes. As I understand it, iceblock does not work against the tornadoes. As [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=46753#comments:id=1317140]pthor1234 [/url] mentions, you should be saving it for phase 2. [b]Paladins:[/b] As I understand it, divine shield doesn't work against the tornadoes. As [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=46753#comments:id=1317140]pthor1234 [/url] mentions, you should be saving it for phase 2. [b]Warlocks: [/b]Warlocks can use their self portal (demonic circle?) to teleport themselves through the tornadoes. [b]Warriors:[/b] Warriors ca", "creationdate": "2011-01-27T22:25:58-06:00", "id": 477662, "rating": 17, "commentid": 1312550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "NobodyYouKnow", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Another little warrior trick I discovered as a fury warrior: If you manage to chain Lightning Strike off of yourself onto someone else, and they die as a result of it, you'll be able to use victory rush. Apparently killing some of your own faction this way is the same as killing a monster. o_O", "creationdate": "2011-02-07T22:19:31-06:00", "id": 222680, "rating": 21, "commentid": 1312550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "NobodyYouKnow", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For sure mate, my death knight friends have been called monsters since they created their toon.  Even getting rotten apples thrown at them!", "creationdate": "2011-02-09T22:06:56-06:00", "id": 223414, "rating": 13, "commentid": 1312550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "475201", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[b]Warlocks:[/b] Demonic Portal can also be used to negate Wind Burst (\u00e0 la Lich King) making your positioning much less important - run through tornadoes whenever you need to and port out of Wind Burst.  [b]Mages:[/b] A similar tactic may be possible, blinking immediately after Wind Burst to remain in the same spot.", "creationdate": "2011-02-14T12:16:17-06:00", "id": 225028, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1312550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "tilgare", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Priest: You can Leap of Faith someone off the Tornadoe.", "creationdate": "2011-02-23T15:55:14-06:00", "id": 227715, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1312550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "phoenixia", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-27T22:26:25-06:00", 1, "NobodyYouKnow"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 1317140, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "pthor1234", "body": "For all paladins, mages and death knights, you can drop the acid rain debuff in P2 to help out your healers when you stack starts to get a bit high.\r\n\r\nMages of course can just ice block, and paladins can bubble.  Death knights take a little bit of timing, because the debuff gets refreshed each 15 seconds, and the duration of AMS is only 7 seconds when glyphed.\r\n\r\nIt may not seem like much, but 3 people dropping their debuffs at 10 stacks is 18k DPS pre-nature resistance that your healers don't have to heal, and may enable to you take a little bit longer in p2.", "date": "2011-01-31T14:48:26-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Rogues can Cloak of Shadows their Acid Rain DoT off as well. In fact, with the CD on CloS you should never have more than 6 stacks of the DoT on you.", "creationdate": "2011-02-27T16:27:46-06:00", "id": 228801, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1317140, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "DukeDoom", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 1317202, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hullken", "body": "As a Hunter your best friend in this encounter is [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=781]Disengage[/url] by far. It greatly helps positioning.\r\nWhen the boss uses [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87770]Wind Burst[/url] you can with this spell ignore moving into melee range and instead standing still, dpsing and disengage back to the platform when he throws you off.\r\nYou can also use this ability to avoid [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93260]Ice Storm[/url] and tornados easier.\r\nHaving this ability glyphed and specced doesn't hurt, especially not in this fight.\r\n\r\nEdit: Remember to have this spell bound to an easy to reach button, I use the middle mouse button. Mixing quick reactions with Disengage helps a lot.", "date": "2011-01-31T15:55:36-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-31T15:58:13-06:00", 1, "Hullken"]}
