{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 1345457, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kragtiki", "body": "Since no one appears to have put this in..\r\n\r\n\r\nLoot is contained in :\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/object=207891]Heart of Wind[/url]", "date": "2011-02-21T23:55:30-06:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 1346449, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "septimx", "body": "warriors, it is possible to use \"heroic leap\" when you're grabbed by tornadoes, and thrown out of the platform, wait for it to throw you, then use heroic leap and land on the platform, make sure you're timing is good, else \"no path available\" will greet you...\n\nthe storm clouds in P3, is quite hard to see (i hope they make clouds darker), especially when you're melee class and its recommended to close in to the boss, the others behind you just tell you when to move up or down, depending on where you start p3...\n\nmanaged to down him a few hours ago with this strategy we read off somewhere: (Feb27)\n\nP3 Strat, Start Top most, go down once to eye level, go down another to shoulder level, go down to bottom, go to knee level, go to waist level, go to top most again because by this time storm clouds have dissipitated, then repeat... he should be down by the time you reach shoulder level again... good luck to all...", "date": "2011-02-22T19:43:00-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-27T21:56:06-06:00", 2, "septimx"]}
