{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 1431918, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "837005", "body": "Thanks. Just two questions:\r\n\r\n1. We can move BEFORE the cloud starts to damage anyone? I think we can only see it when it damages us hardly and maybe we start to move too late?\r\n\r\n2. The cloud placed on the horizontally lowest raid member or on a random raid member?\r\n\r\nThanks a lot!", "date": "2011-06-01T07:09:50-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirming what kovachattack above says: the lightning cloud starts at a random raid member, thus why it's really important that your raiders aren't spread out vertically - it's cruicial that they are more or less at the same altitude - and rather loosely spread out horizontally (some closer to the boss, some at a little range, some left and some right etc) - whoever gets the Lightning Rod on them should move sideways a bit away from the others until it wears off. Have everyone move together up or down depending on where you start. This can be seen fairly well in the video posted earlier in th", "creationdate": "2011-06-01T07:09:51-05:00", "id": 485818, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1431918, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Euphemia", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 1433072, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "585478", "body": "[quote]Thanks. Just two questions:\r\n\r\n1. We can move BEFORE the cloud starts to damage anyone? I think we can only see it when it damages us hardly and maybe we start to move too late?\r\n\r\n2. The cloud placed on the horizontally lowest raid member or on a random raid member?\r\n\r\nThanks a lot![/quote]\r\n\r\nThe cloud appears horizontally at the altitude of a random raid member. Thus, it is ideal to have all raid members at the same altitude, starting at either the top or the bottom, and when a cloud forms, everyone moves together either up or down, depending on where you started, to get out of it. And yes, you have something like 2 seconds after the cloud forms before it becomes filled with lightning and starts to damage people.", "date": "2011-06-03T00:09:18-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
