{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 1683860, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hairband", "body": "In 4.3.4, this boss is still hard but not because of your DPS.  It's hard because of mechanics.  You need one tank and someone with some tank abilities (DK was perfect with Death Grip) to pull the Stormlings in Phase 2.  Also, don't release or you will be locked out.  \r\n\r\nTry to focus on this strat (10 man run):\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Phase 1--Probably the Hardest Phase:[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nThe most important thing is to avoid the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=91110]Squall Line[/url].  You need to call on Vent:  \"Clockwise front\", \"Clockwise middle\", \"Clockwise back\", or \"Counter front\", \"Counter middle\", Counter back\".  This is because two Squall lines are going to be moving around, in a circle, on Al'Akir's platform.  You DO get about 5 seconds lead time by way of a dusty graphic on the ground, to show you where the Squall Line will form so get the hell off of that spot.  Get used to moving into these holes, but trying to stay inside your wedge on the platform (i.e., don't go right or left but try to remain on your fleur de lis spread out), and your party can move pretty freely to find that hole, center yourself because you do get snagged sometimes, and safely stand in the hole of the Squall Line.  Squall line can kill you but if you are lucky enough to ONLY get a knock back, you lose 10 seconds of time, which just prolongs this annoying fight.\r\n\r\nSecondly, once that's under control, you have to hug him like your best pal when he does a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87770]Wind Burst[/url].  However, if you are trying to make a break for the Squall Line at the same time, just let yourself fall off.  If you have DBM and its sound on, you do get a nice warning sound for every Wind Burst.  I just called out \"Hug him\" for every Wind Burst---no one forgot what to do by the end of the fight.\r\n\r\nAs for the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93257]Lightning Strike[/url] conal web attack: it is not that bad.  Our healers had plenty of mana to heal through it--and yes, we did  really open up for this, 2-3 people on each Fleur de Lis shape, all doing a range check for the healers.  There is no reason to stack for this, the conal attack is 60 degrees.\r\n\r\nIf you just call out the Squall Line and listen and call out the Wind Burst, you can get the feel for this Phase and get through.  People were saying front, back, etc. but without the Clock or Counter, you sometimes would hit one before the other and get stuck.\r\n\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Phase 2:[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nYou still get the wonderful Squall Line and Wind Burst, just like in Phase 1, but you will notice Phase 2 rolls around when Al'Akir is 80% health and the first Stormling appears.  At that time, tank pulls around the back of the party and the party gets into a formation of melee in front and ranged in the back with healers able to reach both groups.\r\n\r\nTanks, if you are out of range due to a knockback from the Wind Burst, regain aggro ASAP or else someone will get your Electrocute.  It hurts bad and you want to have a healer in range of you---DPS should not taking it.  Inevitably, some DPS will take it but hopefully will get healed back up.  \r\n\r\nTank stays at opposite end of all DPS, ideally.  Melee DPS (not necessarily an OT but someone not squishy) will pick up [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=47175]Stormlings[/url].  Ranged, you don't want these on you; please AOE them down.  Each one down gives you a 20 second debuff to help you kill the boss called [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87904]Feedback[/url].  The Stormlings are called about once every 20 seconds so you can keep these rolling.  Immediately after killing a Stormling, get back on the boss.  \r\n\r\nAfter maybe about 8 of these Stormlings die and you move defensively, just as you did in Phase 1, at around 25%, you will be done with Phase 2.\r\n\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Phase 3:[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nAt 25%, Al'Akir's platform crumbles.  You will note at his feet there are a weblike lighting structure--do not go there.  They will kill you.  You can fly around and get the feel for the movement, but basically you spread out at his feet (some say head, that's fine), and start the dps.  The three positions basically are feet, his belly button, and his head (also this is the ceiling of the Storm).  Get used to everyone moving, preferably to a marked raid leader, to the same vertical spot, though spread around, for this fight.  Feet, belly, head, belly, head, etc. are the positions you will take depending on where you need to move to.\r\n\r\nYou still get the Wind Bursts from Phases 1 & 2, which are now instant casts instead of having maybe 5 seconds cast lead time.  You get one party who has to run out due to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93294]Lightning Rod[/url].  They need to stay at the same vertical height, just back up aways until it passes and ready to move up if the party moves up.  \r\n\r\nThen, every 30 seconds or so, a zone of Al'Akir vertically will be deadly due to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93298]Lightning Clouds[/url].  This basically is the reason you move from feet, belly, head, belly, etc. to try to find a clear zone.  So you are going to be moving from the Lightning Clouds, hug him for the Wind Bursts, and if you get Lightning Rod, back up from the party.  The key to movement is everyone stay the same and follow the leader you designate.\r\n\r\n\r\nThat's it!  Phase 1 is definitely the hardest, and once you get that, Phase 2 will be easy.  Then, Phase 3 is really weird and fast, and we wiped plenty of times at 4% boss health but we eventually did it with some new raiders who wanted to see the instance and were geared in Hour of Twilight or LFR.", "date": "2012-07-03T02:33:29-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 1862515, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "622946", "body": "Good news for [b]mages[/b], this guy is currently (5.3) soloable through sheer DPS.\r\n\r\nUpdate for [b]monks[/b]: with 550+ Al'Akir 25 is killable in BM, with 560+ in WW (for WW do not forget remove [url=http://wowhead.com/item=90715]this glyph[/url]), conclave is also soloable starting from Anshal, then going to Nezir and using [url=http://wowhead.com/spell=122470]karma[/url] to catch a break and heal yourself)\r\n\r\nThe comfortable DPS is in 120k sustainable range, because you should outdps his [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=88301]Acid rain[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=88427]Electrocute[/url]. You can postpone your death by running to melee thus stopping [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=88427]Electrocute[/url] from ramping up and go back to range, resetting it.\r\nHis [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=47175]adds[/url] can be rooted by Frost nova, but it is easier to kill them instantly (their spawn rate is enough to keep [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=87904]buff[/url] rolling).\r\n\r\nDepending on your gear you will spend different time healing in 2nd phase, from occasionally poping Ice Barrier to constantly casting Evocate and praying. The third phase is instant win.\r\n\r\nThere isn't any requirements for mage-specific abilities, so any decent geared class (with some self-healing) can solo it. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[s]Rather unfortunately  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=45871]Conclave[/url] is still unsoloable because of evading. :([/s]\r\n\r\nP.S. With 550+ something conclave is easily killed by mage (start from Rohash, skip -haste with Ice Block; evading is caused by Anshal's adds at 35-40 energy, so leave your copies on Nezir and kill Anshal second, Ice Barrier is of great help)\r\n\r\nHope this helps and good luck with mount.", "date": "2013-06-04T00:54:44-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Conclave is very solo'able by Warriors. I do it every week to get to Al'Akir for my mount chance. Read some of the newer comments to see how its done :-)", "creationdate": "2013-11-21T05:15:47-06:00", "id": 709627, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1862515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "smackthekids", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-03-12T17:09:35-05:00", 4, "622946"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 1886959, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Scampson", "body": "Easy solo for Blood DK in ilvl 504 DPS Gear.\r\n-PHASE ONE-\r\nBasic phase. Watch for Squall Lines and move towards him when he casts Wind Burst to avoid falling off the side. Lasts from 100% to 80%.\r\n-PHASE TWO-\r\nBasically Phase One with some adds. If your DPS is low, consider killing some of the adds to increase the damage Al'Akir takes. Lasts from 80% to 25%.\r\n-PHASE THREE-\r\nThis phase is completely different, but not any more difficult.  Start up towards his head and slowly work your way down to avoid taking large amounts of damage from his Lightning Clouds. All adds from Phase Two that were left alive are still alive, so you might need to finish them off, or just fly around the boss in circles, they will not catch you unless you stop moving. Use Anti Magic Shell if you need to pass through a Lightning Cloud for any reason. Lightning Rod will deal pretty hefty damage if you don't time your Death Strikes while the debuff is up. Lasts from 25% to 0%.\r\n\r\nGood Luck!", "date": "2013-08-14T10:04:49-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
