{"commentv2": 1, "number": 59, "id": 1936584, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "BscorpobBx5", "body": "[b]Soloed all of [zone=5638] for [item=63041] as a 546 BM Hunter with legendary cloak today.[/b]\n\n[b]Preparation: [/b]I don't think it's doable in anything other than Beast Mastery, I found the [spell=90361] from a spirit beast is required. As long as you constantly use [spell=34477] to your pet when on [npc=45871]'s platform, you also shouldn't get any aggro, as I recommend speccing your pet ferocity instead of tenacity, the DPS is needed. Agility food([spell=104275]), [item=49633], and [item=79257] isn't a must but certainly helps. A core hound pre-cast [spell=90355] couldn't hurt either. [spell=56829] and [spell=20895] are required, and I also specced [spell=109306] for this fight, as when no one is on [npc=45872]'s platform, his debuff ([spell=85573]), makes you silenced, preventing you from using [spell=34026].\n\n[b]Strategy (Conclave of Wind): [/b]Start off by bursting down [npc=45870], due to the debuff from the other wind lords, your haste is decreased by 5000%, and you won't be able to use [spell=34026]. Use all your CDs, and try to kill him before you run out of focus. Once [npc=45870] is dead, (you should be 90% health or more) run over to [npc=45871]'s platform. Getting to his platform means you get your haste back, but you are still silenced. [npc=45871] has a very strange aggro table, I actually had to macro [spell=34477] into my attacks for him to not attack me. Get out of the [spell=86111]es ASAP, and stay behind him, as he uses a frontal AoE attack ([spell=86082]).Use [spell=90361] once [npc=45872]'s debuff starts doing a lot of damage. If you get low after that, you can use a [item=76097]. Use any CD's you have to finish [npc=45871], and once he's dead run over to [npc=45872]'s platform. Once you get there it's pretty much a kill, however when he casts [spell=84643], you can still take 300k fall damage, you can avoid this by using [spell=781] right before you hit the floor. All you have to do is kill [npc=45872] before [npc=45870] finishes casting [spell=86307], and it should be a kill.\n\n[b]Strategy ([npc=46753]): [/b]Just avoid Tornadoes ([spell=87856]) and stand close to him so his [spell=87770] don't knock you off, [npc=46753] is a ton easier than the conclave of wind, as long as your in 540+ you can pretty much just burn him. It should be noted though that killing [npc=47175] put a 10% increased damage debuff ([spell=87904]) on [npc=46753], and it does stack, so it is useful to either let them build up, then kill them all at once, or kill them one by one as they spawn. Important: When he knocks you back during phase 3 with [spell=87770], you have to resummon your pet.\n\nYouTube Video of me soloing both bosses: http://youtube.com/watch?v=nVKN-nKhXxg\n\n[b]Good luck solo farming [item=63041] as a hunter, and I hope this comment helped you![/b]\n\n[small]Armory to my hunter: http://us.battle.net/wow/en/character/whisperwind/Scorpob/advanced Feel free to ask me any questions in-game if you are having trouble, or have any questions about the fight, I currently have this on solofarm every week until I get the mount :P[/small]", "date": "2014-01-21T19:12:40-06:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-03-11T21:40:59-05:00", 3, "BscorpobBx5"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 60, "id": 1942378, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gamer1494", "body": "Easily soloed in guardian (probably could have done it in feral) WITH the achievement which appears to no longer be bugged! I soloed conclave as feral beforehand, will try for the Stay Chill achievement next week which I think will require being bear, but might not pull enough dps. Feral only gets 2 energy regen per second with the debuff\n\nThe best strat I've seen for conclave is to burst anshal>nezir then get rohash low and wait for anshal to come back up. kill anshal then finish rohash and you got ~ 1 minute 30 seconds to kill nezir which should be plenty of time to get 7 stacks. this only works if silence isn't a problem", "date": "2014-02-11T06:19:13-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-02-11T06:24:52-06:00", 1, "gamer1494"]}
