{"commentv2": 1, "number": 62, "id": 1984086, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "zookni", "body": "Easily soloed by a SoO normal geared destruction warlock at 10man heroic, do the conclave in 10 normal (leave doomguard at nezir, kill rohash, rush back to anshal, kills his weeds, kill nezir, kill anshal) then you can switch 10hc to Al'Akir. Use soul leech and grimoire of sacrifice. Note that the last phase is the hardest phase, so you can save your cooldowns for that. Start with unending resolve to build up a decent soul leech absorb. Whatever you do, do NOT stand in melee, his electrocute ability hits way less than his melee swing to a warlock and SL eats it up easily. Grimoire of sacrifice fades when the boss destroys the ground, don't bother to summon a new pet for that, it will fade endlessly, just fly around and spam your shadowburn as much as you can with dark soul (you should have 4 embers when you reach the last phase to make it as easy as possible). Kill all the stormlings as quick as possbile (good thing we have havoc), try to get them below 20% to get a shadowburn and extra embers for dmg / heal. At the last phase, do not get caught by lightning cloud, if you do you will wipe probably cause it hits too hard and you cant do anything for the whole duration.\n\nHappy farming.", "date": "2014-07-24T18:02:03-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-07-24T18:03:22-05:00", 1, "zookni"]}
